The paper deals with clustering and distance metrics, which are common topics in computational geometry (cs.CG) and data structures (cs.DS). The use of approximation algorithms and the focus on optimizing the metric for clustering also suggest machine learning (cs.LG) and data mining (cs.DM) as possible sub-categories. Finally, the mention of integrals and optimization hints at numerical analysis (cs.NA) as a potential sub-category.
